#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/payments.rst:145
msgid "Click :guilabel:`Create payment`."
msgstr "按一下\\ :guilabel:`建立付款`\\ 。"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/payments.rst:147
msgid ""
"The invoices or bills are then marked as :guilabel:`In payment` until the "
"bank transactions are :doc:`reconciled <bank/reconciliation>` with the "
"payments."
msgstr ""
"發票或帳單隨後會標記為\\ :guilabel:`付款中`\\ ，直到銀行交易與付款\\ :doc:`核"
"銷 <bank/reconciliation>`\\ 為止。"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/payments.rst:153
msgid ""
"Registering a single payment for multiple customers or vendors (batch "
"payments)"
msgstr "為多個客戶或供應商註冊單一付款（批次付款）"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/payments.rst:155
msgid ""
"Batch payments allow grouping payments from multiple customers to "
"ease :doc:`reconciliation <bank/reconciliation>`. They are also useful when "
"depositing :doc:`checks <payments/checks>` or cash payments to the bank or "
"for generating bank payment files such as :doc:`SEPA <payments/"
"sepa_payments>` or :ref:`NACHA <l10n_us/nacha>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/payments.rst:161
msgid ":doc:`payments/batch`"
msgstr ":doc:`payments/batch`"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/payments.rst:166
msgid "Registering a partial payment"
msgstr "註冊部分付款"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/payments.rst:168
msgid ""
"To register a partial payment, click on :guilabel:`Register Payment` from "
"the related invoice or bill. In the case of a partial payment (when "
"the :guilabel:`Amount` paid is less than the total remaining amount on the "
"invoice or the bill), the :guilabel:`Payment Difference` field displays the "
"outstanding balance. There are two options:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/payments.rst:173
msgid ""
":guilabel:`Keep open`: Keep the invoice or the bill open and mark it with "
"a :guilabel:`Partial` banner;"
msgstr ""
":guilabel:`保持開啟`\\ ：保持發票或帳單為開啟狀態，並以\\ :guilabel:`部分`\\ "
"橫幅標記；"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/payments.rst:175
msgid ""
":guilabel:`Mark as fully paid`: Select an account in the :guilabel:`Post "
"Difference In` field and change the :guilabel:`Label` if needed. A journal "
"entry will be created to balance the accounts payable or receivable with the "
"selected account."
msgstr ""
":guilabel:`標記為已全額付款`\\ ：在\\ :guilabel:`差異過帳至`\\ 欄位中選擇帳"
"戶，並視需要變更\\ :guilabel:`標籤`\\ 。系統會建立日記帳記項，以平衡應付或應"
"收帳款與所選帳戶。"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/payments.rst:None
msgid "register a partial payment"
msgstr "註冊部分付款"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/payments.rst:185
msgid "Reconciling payments with bank transactions"
msgstr "將付款與銀行交易核銷"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/payments.rst:187
msgid ""
"Once a payment has been registered, the status of the invoice or bill "
"is :guilabel:`In payment`. The next step is :doc:`reconciling <bank/"
"reconciliation>` the payment with the related :doc:`bank transaction <bank/"
"transactions>` line to finalize the payment workflow and mark the invoice or "
"bill as :guilabel:`Paid`."
msgstr ""
"付款註冊後，發票或帳單的狀態為\\ :guilabel:`付款中`\\ 。下一步是將付款與相關"
"\\ :doc:`銀行交易 <bank/transactions>`\\ 資料行\\ :doc:`核銷 <bank/"
"reconciliation>`\\ ，以完成付款工作流程並將發票或帳單標記為\\ :guilabel:`已付"
"款`\\ 。"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/payments/batch.rst:5
msgid ""
"Batch payments act as an organizational tool that groups multiple individual "
"customer or vendor payments into a single file. Rather than managing "
"transactions one by one, you can consolidate them to generate a detailed "
"deposit slip or a single electronic payment file. This significantly "
"simplifies :doc:`bank reconciliation <../bank/reconciliation>`: when a bulk "
"sum appears on your bank statement, Odoo uses the batch reference to "
"automatically match and reconcile all underlying payments in a single step."
msgstr ""
"批次付款充當一種組織工具，將多筆個別客戶或供應商付款分組到單一檔案中。您可以"
"整合這些交易，以產生詳細的存款單或單一電子付款檔案，而非逐筆管理交易。這大幅"
"簡化了\\ :doc:`銀行調節 <../bank/reconciliation>`：當銀行對帳單上出現大筆金額"
"時，Odoo 會使用批次參考自動匹配並一次性調節所有基礎付款。"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/payments/batch.rst:12
msgid ""
"For customer payments, the feature supports both physical payments, such "
"as :doc:`checks <checks>` and cash, and electronic transfers. Group incoming "
"cash or check payments into batches to print bank deposit slips to ensure "
"your internal records mirror the lump-sum deposit on your bank statement. On "
"the vendor side, batch payments streamline bulk electronic transfers. "
